umbs__item" aria-current="page">How the Soviet Union’s Fall Pushed Putin to Try and Recapture Russia’s Global Importance</li></ol></nav><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://www.history.com"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Topics","item":"https://www.history.com/topics"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"European History","item":"https://www.history.com/topics/european-history"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":4,"name":"How the Soviet Union’s Fall Pushed Putin to Try and Recapture Russia’s Global Importance"}]}</script><div class="page-header__content"><div class="page-header__content-container"><h1 class="page-header__title">How the Soviet Union’s Fall Pushed Putin to Try and Recapture Russia’s Global Importance</h1><div class="page-header__summary">While serving in the KGB in East Berlin, Putin was shocked and humiliated to experience the collapse of Soviet power firsthand.</div></div></div><div class="page-header__post-info"><div class="page-header__post-info-container"><div class="page-header__author-date"><p class="page-header__author"><span aria-hidden="true">By: </span><a aria-label="Read more articles from Shaun Walker" link-name="Shaun Walker" href="/author/shaun-walker">Shaun Walker</a></p><p>Updated: <time dateTime="2023-08-04T20:48:54">August 4, 2023</time> <!-- --> | <span>Original: <time dateTime="2018-02-23T16:35:13">February 23, 2018</time></span></p></div><div class="page-header__sharing hide-print"><button class="button is-style-standalone is-style-standalone--dark-background has-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24"><path d="M16 1H4C2.9 1 2 1.9 2 3V17H4V3H16V1ZM19 5H8C6.9 5 6 5.9 6 7V21C6 22.1 6.9 23 8 23H19C20.1 23 21 22.1 21 21V7C21 5.9 20.1 5 19 5ZM19 21H8V7H19V21Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg>copy page link</button><button cla